lyrics:
In the winter of December.
I met a lion boy who could burn me,
He is like a wild lion,
Caught my attention and lit up my world.
Dispelling loneliness with a fiery touch
I know I'm falling into a lion's trap,
Gradually lose myself and become the king in my heart.

He is as tall and strong as a lion,
Armed with confidence under the bright sun, 
A proud child with a simple heart.
In this tired world, 
With a roaring heart and such a free spirit, 
Under the starry night, we fit together so well,
He is the sun and I am the moon, 
every time, every moments
In the hot embrace, in the moist warmth, 
In this passion, we find our own rhythme
